1
00:00:11,867 --> 00:00:13,367
I can't reach Mookie.

2
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,100
Flor isn't answering my calls,
too.

3
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:16,567
Mookie, wake up!

4
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:17,467
Mookie!

5
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:19,767
Dear, wake up!

6
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,967
Your wife can't help
but be a mother.

7
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,233
She's happy with what she does
to her employer's daughter.

8
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,700
Is Emma there in your room?

9
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:27,000
She's not here, Mommy.

10
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,067
Why did the screen go black?

11
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:31,633
Mother, why are you
with Ma'am Olive?

12
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,700
I will be your eyes
and ears here.

13
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:38,033
My dream is to travel
to different places.

14
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,867
Danilo, this is Mookie.

15
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,533
Mookie, this is Danilo,

16
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,533
- my husband.
- Hello.

17
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:45,633
- Hello. Hi.
- Come on, have fun!

18
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,600
You're crazy!

19
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,667
Bring that kid home!

20
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,067
It's okay, I can do this.

21
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,000
Thank you.

22
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:54,200
I want to take a picture.

23
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,700
I have a cell phone.

24
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,567
Are you done, Madam?

25
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:38,600
Careful.

26
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:39,767
I got it.

27
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:40,967
What time is it?

28
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:42,567
It's four in the afternoon.

29
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:43,633
Four?

30
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:46,833
I'm so bored.

31
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,967
Slowly, Madam.

32
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:56,800
Mom, I hope this won't be
my last trip to the mall.

33
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,867
I'm sure there will be
a next time.

34
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:03,033
But that seems impossible.

35
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:08,133
I'll be a prisoner again
tomorrow when mommy gets back.

36
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:11,400
Let's not think about it
for now.

37
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,200
Let's just enjoy the moment.

38
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:16,367
There.

39
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,367
There.

40
00:02:23,667 --> 00:02:26,400
Let's cover your feet
so you won't get cold.

41
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:27,233
There you go.
Okay.

42
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,067
This, too.

43
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,900
Wait, are you sure
you're feeling okay?

44
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,467
Yes, Mother.

45
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:38,700
Look.

46
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:42,833
See?

47
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,200
Even though I'm tired,

48
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:47,033
I still can breathe
without my cannula.

49
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,667
It seems like I'm not ill.

50
00:02:49,967 --> 00:02:51,800
Maybe you really aren't...

51
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:56,567
I'm really not what, Mother?

52
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:57,400
What?

53
00:02:58,900 --> 00:02:59,500
No, it's nothing.

54
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:03,100
I forgot what I was going
to say.

55
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:05,333
Wait. Do you want anything?

56
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:08,167
Here.

57
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:09,433
Ice cream.

58
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,233
Sure, Mom.
Do you want some?

59
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,700
All right.

60
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:18,167
Mister, please give me
some ice cream.

61
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:20,867
The cards are everywhere.

62
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:36,733
Why can't I contact them
anymore?

63
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:45,733
The subscriber
cannot be reached...

64
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,400
What's happening?

65
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:50,167
Why can't I call them?

66
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:51,033
Madam.

67
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:53,800
Madam, calm down.

68
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,433
Shut up!

69
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:03,667
Hello?
Hello, Ma'am Olive?

70
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:05,133
Is this the guard?

71
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,900
Yes, Ma'am. I know you.

72
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:07,867
Good.

73
00:04:07,933 --> 00:04:09,000
Check our house

74
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:11,333
because I can't contact
my daughter and her nanny.

75
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:13,367
Now!

76
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,733
- Wow!
- Here you go, Dear.

77
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,500
Thank you, Mother.

78
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,700
You're welcome.

79
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,333
- How is it? Good?
- It's so delicious!

80
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:42,067
They said it's their bestseller.

81
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:45,700
There. Eat that.

82
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:46,900
There.

83
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,600
Pistachios is their bestseller.

84
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:53,800
Is it good?

85
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,667
This is Pistachio!

86
00:04:57,933 --> 00:04:58,633
What?

87
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,000
Are you stupid?

88
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:02,333
Mookie is allergic to nuts!

89
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:06,300
Do you know what can happen
to her with what you did?

90
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:07,800
- I'm sorry, Ma'am!
- Her throat can swell!

91
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:09,633
And she can die!

92
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,367
Mookie?

93
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:14,767
- What's going on?
- Mother...

94
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:15,767
Are you okay?

95
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:18,067
- Mookie?
- Mother.

96
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:19,633
What's happening?

97
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,467
- What?
- Mother.
What is it?

98
00:05:28,767 --> 00:05:32,500
Ma'am Olive, it seems like
there's no one inside.

99
00:05:32,567 --> 00:05:33,567
What?

100
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,800
Look for them in the park.

101
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:36,733
Sorry, Ma'am.

102
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,267
I need to return
to the guard house.

103
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:40,467
I'm sorry.

104
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:40,800
But...

105
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:41,967
Hello!

106
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:47,767
Mookie!

107
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:48,967
Mother, I'm allergic...

108
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:51,433
- to pistachios.
- What?

109
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,867
Let me have this.

110
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:55,433
My god. What should I do?

111
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,033
Do you have a medicine?
What medicine do you take?

112
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:57,733
What do you need?

113
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,967
- I need...
- What?

114
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:00,433
- What is it?
- epinephrine.

115
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,200
What?

116
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:02,467
- Epi...
- Help!

117
00:06:02,533 --> 00:06:03,200
- Help!
- Epinephrine, Mother.
Mister!

118
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:04,667
Yes, Ma'am?

119
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:05,933
Where's the nearest clinic?

120
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,900
Over there, Ma'am.

121
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,033
- Can you please come with us?
- Sure.

122
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,300
- Hold on, Dear.
- Follow me.

123
00:06:10,367 --> 00:06:10,967
Let's go.

124
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,967
I feel that Flor
brought Mookie outside.

125
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:21,800
That's why they're not
answering their phones.

126
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:25,667
Madam, don't stress
yourself out.

127
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:28,400
I'm sure your daughter
is already sleeping.

128
00:06:28,467 --> 00:06:29,600
And your maid, too.

129
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:33,100
They're in your house.
Safe and sound.

130
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:36,100
You're the one in the hospital,
sick.

131
00:06:36,167 --> 00:06:38,767
You should think
about yourself first.

132
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,233
Come on.

133
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,900
Let's play again.

134
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:47,933
I told you, relax.

135
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,500
You might feel sick again.

136
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:56,533
There.

137
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,500
Okay, inhale...

138
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:00,233
exhale, Madam.

139
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:01,900
Say "ah."

140
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:11,667
No rashes.

141
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:12,800
No itchiness.

142
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,367
And your throat
is perfectly normal.

143
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:19,033
Are you sure you're allergic
to pistachios?

144
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:24,300
Yes, that's what my mom said.

145
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:27,467
You've eaten a lot.

146
00:07:27,533 --> 00:07:29,700
If you're allergic
to pistachios,

147
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:33,033
you should've suffered from
severe throat irritation,

148
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,467
or some rashes.

149
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:39,133
Doc, she was having a hard time
breathing earlier.

150
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,600
I suspect that was a panic
attack.

151
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:44,767
I suggest you discuss this
incident with your doctor.

152
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,867
Because I don't think
she's allergic to pistachios.

153
00:07:55,367 --> 00:08:02,267
So, does it mean mommy
made a wrong diagnosis?

154
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:03,933
We're not sure.

155
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,700
But isn't it good

156
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:08,900
that we learned you're not
allergic to pistachios?

157
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,333
Yes.

158
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:25,767
Madam, here are the clothes
you asked me to buy.

159
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,067
Where did you buy it?

160
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:29,333
In Divisoria.

161
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,133
It looks good.

162
00:08:31,633 --> 00:08:33,000
Do you want to see it?

163
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:34,333
Good morning.

164
00:08:35,733 --> 00:08:38,400
Hi, Ma'am Caparas.
I'll just check your vitals.

165
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:39,033
No need.

166
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,400
That's not necessary.

167
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:42,133
I feel better now.

168
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,300
I want to go home.

169
00:08:43,367 --> 00:08:46,467
But Ma'am,
Dr. Taplac said...

170
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:48,400
I'm a doctor, too.

171
00:08:48,467 --> 00:08:50,400
I can take care of myself.

172
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:51,700
Now, tell Dr. Taplac

173
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:55,267
that I will sign the discharge
without medical advice form.

174
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:56,067
Now.

175
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:06,367
Madam, that's impressive.

176
00:09:07,467 --> 00:09:08,933
I didn't know you're a doctor,
too.

177
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:13,233
Shouldn't you follow
what your co-doctors say?

178
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:16,067
Stay here and regain
your strength first.

179
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:18,200
Am I asking for your opinion?

180
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,033
No.

181
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,800
I want to go home.

182
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:22,267
Give me my crutches.

183
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,233
Oh!

184
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,867
I won't allow you.

185
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:26,267
What right do you have?

186
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:32,033
Madam, aren't we somewhat
close friends?

187
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,667
You're no longer
a stranger to me.

188
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:36,200
I'm concerned about your health.

189
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:40,000
So, let's just do
what the doctor said.

190
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:41,400
Get some rest here.

191
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:42,333
Okay?

192
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,233
Why don't you want me
to go home?

193
00:09:46,367 --> 00:09:48,833
Maybe you know
what's happening to my daughter.

194
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,933
Has it happened to you before?

195
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,400
Did you have an allergic
reaction to pistachios?

196
00:09:56,467 --> 00:09:58,133
Yes, on my birthday.

197
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,467
Did you get
an allergic reaction?

198
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:05,667
Mom gave me epinephrine
right away.

199
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:08,067
You know, the doctor was right.

200
00:10:09,533 --> 00:10:11,733
If you're allergic
to pistachios,

201
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,967
something bad should've happened
because you've eaten a lot.

202
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:18,433
I'm also confused, Mother.

203
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,933
Look at me now.

204
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,333
I'm still okay, right?

205
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,233
Maybe you should
talk to your mom.

206
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:34,033
What did your daughter tell you?

207
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,533
I'm not talking to her.

208
00:10:35,633 --> 00:10:36,833
She isn't answering my calls.

209
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,233
Don't you dare lie to me!

210
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,567
Madam, I'm just worried
about you.

211
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,767
- Give me my crutches!
- I'm not...

212
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:48,000
- Wait! You might fall!
- Give me my crutches...

213
00:10:48,067 --> 00:10:49,267
Sit down. I'll get it for you.

214
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:49,867
Give it to me!

215
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:51,300
Yes, Ma'am. Wait.

216
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,633
I'm not lying.
I'm just concerned about you.

217
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,433
- Why are you so eager
- I said give it to me!

218
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:57,733
to get home?

219
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:02,467
You can go home tomorrow once
you get your clearance, anyway.

220
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,167
You're right.

221
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:08,800
I'll get discharged tomorrow.

222
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,533
What's another night?

223
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,000
Thanks for the concern.

224
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:16,500
Anyway...

225
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,200
I'm hungry.

226
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:20,700
Oh, what do you like, Madam?

227
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:24,900
There's a nearby
Yuen Mio branch here.

228
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:29,600
Can you buy me
my favorite ebi sushi?

229
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:30,833
Ebi sushi?

230
00:11:31,867 --> 00:11:33,500
Ebi sushi.

231
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:41,933
Get yourself some food, too.

232
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,233
Thank you.

233
00:11:47,033 --> 00:11:48,733
I'll be quick. Wait for me.

234
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:26,633
Mommy might get mad at me
if I ask her about my condition.

235
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:31,067
She might say I don't trust her.

236
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:38,800
Why don't you ask Ma'am Astrid
when she comes back from Cebu?

237
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:49,800
Bros, wait.

238
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:55,467
Mookie, you're here.

239
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,233
Zayn?

240
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,000
Hi.

241
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:01,067
Hello.

242
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:03,633
I'm Zayn, Mookie's friend.

243
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,633
Hello, I'm Emma.
I'm their laundress.

244
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:08,367
Nice to meet you, Emma.

245
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,600
Are you going to play
in the arcade?

246
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:13,133
We were here earlier.

247
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,100
But we didn't bring any money.

248
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:16,300
Come on, let's play.

249
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:17,167
My treat.

250
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:19,733
Will that be okay, Emma?

251
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,100
If that's okay with Mookie.

252
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:23,333
Is it okay with you, Mookie?

253
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,000
That's okay with her.

254
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:26,100
Right, Mookie?

255
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:33,233
Is it your first time
being in the mall?

256
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:36,133
Well, you know why, right?

257
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,200
Oh, yeah.

258
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:40,700
Your mom has never
allowed you to go out.

259
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:42,300
Sorry.

260
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:45,033
But I'm glad
she let you go out now.

261
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,700
She doesn't know.

262
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:49,500
And she shouldn't know.

263
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:51,300
Your secret is safe with me.

264
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,533
Come on, let's play.

265
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,900
Where do we go first?

266
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,100
Do you want to try
the motorbike?

267
00:13:58,167 --> 00:13:59,900
How can I do that?

268
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:00,500
Let's go.

269
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:01,867
Watch me first.

270
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:03,433
Here, here.

271
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,233
I'll show you.

272
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,333
Stay there.

273
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,800
OMG!

274
